# I/O, Input, View & App

## Stdin protocol (do not change without explicit request)

1. Board rows until `Board:` marker (or legacy: rows then `Commands:`)
2. Commands: `click X Y`, `jump X Y`, `wait MS`, `print board`
3. Errors to stdout: `ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN`, `ERROR ROW_WIDTH_MISMATCH`, etc.
4. `main.cpp` wires `ScriptParser` + `BoardPrinter` into `ScriptRunner` and runs the whole protocol via
   `ScriptRunner::run(std::cin, std::cout)` — no hardcoded demo

## Layer roles

| Layer | Does | Does not |
|-------|------|----------|
| `io/` | Parse/print board text | Validate moves |
| `input/` | Map pixels/clicks → `Position` | Hold game state |
| `view/` | Render `GameSnapshot` | Mutate `Board` |
| `App` | Wire engine + I/O + input + view | Implement piece rules |

## Input flow

```
stdin → ScriptParser → ScriptRunner → Controller → GameEngine → snapshot → BoardPrinter
```

- `BoardMapper`: pixel `(x, y)` → grid `Position` using cell size constant
- `Controller`: translate `click` into `requestMove(from, to)` based on selection state (clicking another
  same-color piece re-targets the selection instead of requesting a move); translate `jump` directly into
  `requestJump(at)`
- `ScriptParser`: parses the `Board:`/`Commands:` protocol into a `Board` + `ScriptCommand` list; implements
  the `IScriptSource` interface (command DTOs live in `texttests/ScriptCommand.h`)
- `ScriptRunner`: replays parsed commands against a fresh `GameEngine`/`Controller`, writing `print board`
  output; receives its `IScriptSource` and `IBoardPrinter` collaborators by const reference through its
  constructor (dependency injection). `main.cpp` is the composition root: it constructs the concrete
  `ScriptParser`/`BoardPrinter`, wires them into `ScriptRunner`, then calls `run(std::cin, std::cout)`

## View flow

- Receive `GameSnapshot` const reference or value copy
- No direct `Board` access; all display data comes from the snapshot DTO
- Keep rendering logic free of rule checks

## Exception handling

### I/O (`io/`)

- Expected parse failures → `BoardParseStatus` + stdout codes (`ERROR UNKNOWN_TOKEN`, etc.) — not exceptions
- Throw `std::runtime_error` only for broken streams; let `ScriptRunner` catch
- `BoardPrinter`: throw on bad stream; no try-catch wrapper

### Input (`input/`)

- `BoardMapper::pixelToCell`: return `std::nullopt` for off-board pixels — no exceptions for normal input
- `BoardMapper` constructor: throw on invalid dimensions
- `Controller::click` / `jump`: catch unexpected errors → status DTO with `runtime_error`; clear selection on failure

### View (`view/`)

- `Img`: validate and throw (missing file, bad draw rect) — no try-catch; `graphics_main` is the top catcher

### Text tests & app

- `ScriptParser`: throw on malformed command syntax or unreadable stream; propagate to `ScriptRunner`
- `ScriptRunner::run`: **the** recovery boundary for the stdin app — single catch, log to `stderr`, `ERROR RUNTIME_FAILURE` to stdout
- `main`: outer safety net — catch, log, exit non-zero
